nts on melee range.  Yes, you may not be able to turn PoP level mobs, but it's rediculously easy to turn a fire or ice giant if your spells do that much of his hp in one blast.  Some of the post 50/60 crowd is still in family type guilds, while I'm not, I still remember what it's like.  If you draw the duty of helping with the clear for your lower members' Vox/Naggy raid, it can be really annoying to get handed a beatdown by a blue or green mob.  <br>
<br>
Melee range is a liability in these situations, since your tanks aren't all that concerned with why the mob isn't hitting them anymore, just that it doesn't seem to be moving out of the horde of swinging tanks.  If the mob had to at least take 3 steps in your direction to connect, that would let the slower tanks out there know that they needed to punch the taunt key or have the enchanter mez it a second so they weren't going to carry a freshly rezzed wizard the next few battles.  Also, if all battles occur in melee range, how am I going to be able to med?  Sit aggro is a bitch that close in.<br>
<br>
That said, yes these do suffer quite a bit from balance issues.  I'm not entirely sure how to save the idea beyond tweaking the mana vs. dmg aspect some more and possibly adding a lower aggro component to it.  If it cost more, but didn't annoy the mob quite as much as it should, that would still make it viable.  <br>
<br>
Some of the others on this thread have brought up some good ideas though.  I like the idea of group harvest/group flappy-effects.  Part of the benefit of that is it really breaks up the holy trinity aspect of the game.  With everyone getting mana, you move away from the adding another support tank to the mix mentality and actually create demand for casters in groups, so you don't waste any of that mana.  It's always bugged me that there are so few pure caster groups.  <br>
<br>
One possible problem with the idea of a sub-par clarity spell for us is that we end up leaving out mages from the mana regen club. Yes, mod rods are mana regen, and yes they are easily utilized when paired with Phantom armor regens and AA skills.  Problem is that this is essentially banked mana, it's not being created from somewhere like harvest, lich, or clarity lines.  With the time limits imposed on rods and all, it's about the same as our harvest line in terms of utility.  Without coming up with a similar skill for mages, we end up creating a new bottom rung of the mana ladder, and just swap one imbalance for another.  <br>
<br>
I won't argue that we don't need a little extra oomph, especially at the pre-60 stage, though.  Yes, you can get a non-AE group in Seb, Velks, or HS before this stage, but how useful do you feel, and how wanted do you think you are?<br>
<br>
Zerlatik Flaimweaver<br>
Sorcerer of Tholuxe Paells<br>
&lt;Paradigm Nocturne&gt;<br>
&quot;It is up to people like you and me who are out of our tiny little minds to try and help these people overcome their sanity&quot; - Graham Chapman. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taelenskychaser>Taelen Skychaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/28/03 9:55:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26268.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Problem</span><hr size=1> Wizards DPS rocks, especially our burst DPS.  A group requires DPS, and a wizard is a great choice for that function.  A rogue is a great choice for DPS.  So is a mage.  There are a ton of classes which can be used for DPS.  It's great having two wizards in a group for your DPS.  But who wants two clerics, or two warriors, or two enchanters?  Wizards are great for groups.  We also provide evac and some crowd control which is something other DPS classes do not provide.  What we need, and what a lot of other classes need, is something that makes us unique outside of our DPS, something that is noticeable, something that makes groups want us.  But I think the problem still remains that every group needs a healer, slower, tank, and the rest of the classes are ffa.  The problem is more that there are not enough people playing the trinity classes and too many people playing the DPS classes, so you end up with a lot of the DPS classes LFG, or a bunch of the DPS classes making a group and looking for a slower, or healer, or tank for a long long time.  I'm not sure how to fix that...  <br>
<br>
But I'd start by making all classes more well rounded.  That's right, I'd give every class more abilities so that it wouldn't be the end of the world when you couldn't find a tank, a slower, or a healer.  Give wizards the ability to cast a weaker form of clarity, have a weaker slow/speed ability.  Give the necro the same type of abilities. That way if you couldn't find a slower you could substitute a necro or wizard.  They already improved the healer situation by giving shamans and druids complete heal type lines, but shamans were already one of the slower classes.  But hey, make Necro heals better maybe or SK heals, definitely Ranger and Pally heals.  A Pally could never act as a main tank and main healer, but if you had two Pally's the second one could fulfill the role of the primary healer, or a Ranger could.  Mages already have mod rods for mana regen, but that's no substitute for an enchanter.  So give mages the ability to summon something that would slow the mob.  I mean, come on, a mage could summon strands of webs or something that would wrap around a mob and slow their movements, but maybe don't give them any speed ability.<br>
<br>
Wo, am I rambling or what.  I just think that the real problem lies in that a group HAS to have a Healer, Slower, and Main Tank.  It's a necessity to have all 3.  Five people can be sitting there and need a slower.  Five people can be sitting there and need a healer, or a tank...  It's ridiculous.  Make Rangers better able to tank.  I don't know...  but just do something to make it not so hard to form groups unless you just know a ton of people.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzitay>Azzitay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/03 5:53:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26268.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Problem</span><hr size=1> Very Good Ideas here ...<br>
